NAME
deconstruct_msg - Parse a message.
SYNOPSIS
#include <mgemessage.h>

struct mgemessage *deconstruct_msg(struct mgemessage *msg);

DESCRIPTION
deconstruct_msg() parses the message field of the mgemessage struct and
populates the struct with the individual elements.

mge_errno is set as required.
PARAMETERS
msg - a pointer to the mgemessage struct to populate. This must be a complete
message.

RETURN VALUE
Return value is a pointer to the fully populated mgemessage struct or NULL on
error.

ERRORS
mge_errno is set as required.

If an incomplete message is passed to this function, NULL is returned and
mge_errno is set to MGE_INVAL_MSG.
